tournaments.about:
Belgian Carcassonne League - Spring Season 2026

The Belgian Carcassonne League (BCL) is a national online league played twice per year on Board Game Arena.


📅 Dates
Spring Season: March 2 – May 31, 2026


🧩 Format
• Round-robin league system (each player plays every other player)
• One match every 2 weeks
• All matches: 1v1, Best of 3, real-time


🏆 Leagues
• Master League – 2 divisions of 7 players
Division winners play a cross final for the season title
• Gold League – 6–12 players (estimated Elo 400+)
• Silver League – 6–12 players (estimated Elo 100–400)
• Bronze League – launched if enough participants register


🔁 Promotion & Relegation
• Two players are promoted from each league
• 1st place: direct promotion
• 2nd place: promotion playoff
• Bottom player is relegated
• Final promotion rules are confirmed before the season starts


👑 Winners
• The Master League cross-final winner is crowned Belgian League Spring Season Champion
• Spring and Autumn champions will later play for the title Belgian League Champion 2026


📝 Registration
Open to players with Belgian nationality or residence.

Register:
• via the Carcassonne Belgium website
• or by email: carcassonnebelgium@hotmail.com


Full rules and structure are available on the tournament website https://carcassonnebelgium.weebly.com/introduction--rules-bcl-2026.html

tournaments.about:
China Carcassonne 2v2 Team Tournament
This tournament brings back the classic 2v2 team format, which used to be a popular way to enjoy Carcassonne on earlier platforms, before the community moved to Board Game Arena (BGA) in 2020 for the first edition of WTCOC. The goal is to offer a competitive but nostalgic team experience in a modern tournament setting.

All matches are played on Board Game Arena (BGA).

Format
The tournament consists of two stages and does not use group stages.

Stage 1 – Swiss System

  1. Swiss system to rank all participating teams
  2. No groups
  3. Results determine the top 4 teams

Stage 2 – Playoffs
  1. Single Elimination
  2. Final match (gold) and bronze medal match are played between the top 4 teams

Game Rules
  1. Game mode: 4-player game, friendly mode on BGA
  2. Team score is the sum of both players’ scores
  3. Teammates must sit in positions 1 & 3 or 2 & 4
  4. If this condition is not met, the game must be restarted

Registration
Registration deadline: February 7, 2026
Open to players from any association.
To register or ask questions, contact qazxswedc on BGA.

tournaments.about:
The Belgian Carcassonne Online Championship 2026 (BCOC 2026) is the annual national online tournament that crowns the Belgian Online Champion and selects representatives for international competitions.

All matches are played on Board Game Arena (BGA) – 1vs1, Best of 3, real-time.


Registration

Open to Belgian citizens or residents.
Players must use their main BGA account, join Carcassonne Belgium on BGA, and register by email at: carcassonnebelgium@hotmail.com.


Tournament Format
• Group Stage: round-robin in several groups
• Top players advance to the Playoffs
• Playoffs: single elimination, Best of 3
• Premium players may create match tournaments; organisers assist if needed


Fair Play
External tools, notes, or assistance are not allowed.
Running out of time results in a game loss.


Qualification
The champion receives a direct CCL ticket and may represent Belgium at international events.
Top 3 players earn places in Team Belgium for WTCOC.


Full rules and details:
https://carcassonnebelgium.weebly.com/introduction–rules.html

tournaments.about:
The Christmas Dream Team Cup is a special holiday Carcassonne team event in a 3-vs-3 format, featuring captains, a player draft, and true “dream team” lineups.


📅 Dates
December 20–21 (Saturday–Sunday)


✨ Tournament Format

Teams
• 6 teams total, each team = 1 captain + 4 drafted players
• All matches are played 3 vs 3

Saturday – League Stage
1 group of 6 teams
Each team plays 2 random matches

Sunday – Playoffs
#1–#2 in the league table advance directly to the semifinals
#3–#6 play quarterfinals (3rd vs 6th, 4th vs 5th)
Winners advance to the semifinals
Then Final + 3rd place match


👑 Captains & Player Draft
Captains are selected from winners of major tournaments held during the year:
1. Serhii (zaharik) – National Team Captain
2. Andrii (Chemimaru) – Ukrainian Champion 2025
3. Maksym (bazilyuk) – Super League & Turn-based Champion
4. Kyrylo (adrear) – Ukrainian Cup Winner
5. Vitalii (Tor_UA) – 2nd place in Turn-based Championships
6. Tanya (TanyaU) – joker-captain chosen by organizers

Before the tournament, a player draft will be held.
Captains will take turns selecting players from the qualified player pool to form their teams.


📝 Registration & Player Selection
Registration is open to all members of the community.

To maintain the format, we need exactly 24 drafted players (4 per captain).

If more than 24 players register:
• The top 24 by peak BGA Elo will enter the draft pool
• Remaining players will go to a reserve list (used if someone withdraws before the event)


Registration form:
👉 https://forms.gle/hgKFojkWszDiUXy19

tournaments.about:
Sign-up form: CLICK
Received sign-ups: SPREADSHEET

Eligibility: Each player may participate in only ONE online national championship per tournament season. Only someone who either has the Czech citizenship or lives temporarily / permanently in Czechia may participate.

Important dates:
• Registration: August 2 up to August 24 23:59
• Tournament draw: August 25
• Tournament start: September 1
• Tournament end: Between October and Mid-November (according to the number of players).

Tournament format:
• Each pair of players will play one Best of Three (BO3) match together.
• During the draw, all matches will be scheduled for their respective weeks. Each player will be scheduled to play at most one match per week.
• The players must agree on the exact time their match will be played. When agreed, one of the players must fill out a form indicating that time. Players will in turn receive a tournament invitation.
• All games are played on BGA using the base game Tournament format with 15 minutes clock time for each player.
• In case of a game ending in a tie, the win goes to the player who has not started (as usual on BGA).
• Final results will be determined by, subsequently, the number of won matches, the difference of games won and lost, and the number of games won. In case of a tie, these criteria will be applied once more, but this time using only the matches between the tied players.
• In the unlikely event of more than 12 entrants, the format will be changed to an 8-round swiss system.

Prizes: The winners will receive the opportunity to represent Czechia in the next Carcassonne Champions League (CCL) season, according to the coefficient update after this year's ETCOC.
tournaments.name: Czech Online National Championship 2025
tournaments.rules:
Tournament rules:

• Players are expected to play and attempt to win all the matches they are supposed to play in.
• Players are expected to complete their matches in a timely manner, allowing sufficient options for match scheduling. Ideally, matches should be scheduled around the beginning of the week. If a player knows they are going to be busy, it is desirable to schedule matches even earlier to avoid backlogs.
• If a player does not come to a match, we will ask the players to reschedule at earliest convenience.
• If it appears there are substantial issues with the timely completion of matches, the team captain might introduce a warning system akin to the one CCL 2025 used.
• If a player is out of time in a game (signaled by the red clock after the game ends), they lose the game, but not the match.
• Players must inform their opponents in case they discard a tile.
• Players may not use any tile-counters, scripts, or any assistance by other humans or AIs during the game.

tournaments.about:
The German Carcassonne Online Championship 2025 is the first inofficial Carcassonne online championship in Germany. Main purpose is to select German representatives for the Carcassonne Champions League (CCL) 2026 season.

All matches are taking place on Board Game Arena (BGA) following CCL (and if necessary WTCOC) rules.


Registration

Open to German citizens or residents who’ve played at least 20 games of Carcassonne on BGA and did/do/will not participate in another countries’ CCL-qualification (this season).

To register just tell yzemaze (BGA, Discord) you’d like to take part in the GCOC 2025. Registration window closes on 30.09.2025 at 20:00.


Tournament Stages

  1. Group Phase: Likely 4 groups of 4 players playing best-of-3 matches. Top 2 advance to playoffs.

    Seeding into pots of 4 players each according to Elo ratings on BGA shortly after registration window is closed. Players from these pots will be distributed into groups at random. (e.g. Group A: pot 1 player 1, p2p1, p3p4 etc.)

  2. Playoffs: Single elimination, best-of-5.

    Finals have to be played by 09.11.2025 at the latest.

Stages and details are subject to change depending on number of participants.


CCL-Qualification

Winner will get a ticket to the CCL group stage. Depending on the results of the ETCOC 2025 there might be either another direct ticket and 1 qualification ticket available or up to 2 qualification tickets. These will go to 2nd and 3rd place finishers.

The event runs from September 1 to November 2, 2025, with group matches followed by playoffs. Taiwan Carcassonne Online Championship (TWCOC) 2025 is the first official national Carcassonne online championship for Taiwan. It is also the qualification tournament to select Taiwanese representatives for the Carcassonne Champions League (CCL) 2026.

The event is played on the Board Game Arena (BGA) platform in a Best of Three format (first to two wins), following the official WTCOC rules.

The tournament consists of two stages:
• Group Stage – players are divided into groups, playing one match per week.
• Knockout Stage – the top players from each group advance to the single-elimination playoffs.

Eligibility: open to Taiwanese citizens and residents of Taiwan, Penghu, Kinmen, and Matsu. Players must maintain a positive BGA reputation/karma above 50%.

Key Dates:
• Registration closes: August 15, 2025
• Groups announced: August 16, 2025
• Group Stage starts: August 18, 2025

Prizes & Qualification:
• Winner: qualifies directly for the CCL 2026 Main Stage and earns a spot on the Taiwanese national team for WTCOC 2026.
• Runner-up: qualifies for the CCL 2026 Qualification Stage and also joins the WTCOC 2026 Taiwan team.
• Additional prizes, including Carcassonne expansions, will be raffled among players who complete the group stage but do not advance to the top 8.

Organizer:
The tournament is organized by Chen Chuang-Hsin (BGA ID: Eyeba11) with support from the “Carcassonne Taiwan Dojo” YouTube channel, which will assist with live draws and streaming.

All games and stages of the championship are free to join and take place online on BGA.

tournaments.about:
The Argentine Carcassonne League is a tournament with 3 divisions in a pyramidal format, meaning that the number of participants doubles with each lower division. The top division is the Elite Division, which has 8 players. The next division is the Platinum Division, with two groups of 8 players each. The lowest division is the Gold Division, with four groups of 6 players each.

This is the first season of the league, and the divisions were formed according to the highest Elos achieved by the players on BGA. BGA is the platform where the tournament is played.

Each week, players compete in a Best of Three (Bo3) duel. At the end of the round-robin stage:
• In Elite, the player finishing in first place will be the division winner.
• In Platinum, there will be a final between the winners of each group.
• In Gold, there will be semifinals and a final among the winners of the 4 groups.

Only Argentinian players are eligible to participate in the championship.

Dates: August 11 – October 12, 2025


Tournament Link:
https://carcassonne.com.ar/torneos/liga-nacional?division=elite

tournaments.about:
🌍 TECS - Torneo por Equipos Carcassonne Spain


Inspired by the amazing CTCB (Torneio de Times Carcassonne Brasil), Spain is launching its first team-based Carcassonne tournament: TECS (Torneo por Equipos Carcassonne Spain)!


💥 Teams of 4 to 6 players will compete each week in head-to-head matchups. Each matchup will consist of 3 duels (1v1), making it a more accessible format than the WTCOC's usual 5-player structure.


🗓 The tournament starts the week of August 18th, with weekly group stage matchups leading to a knockout final phase.


🇪🇸 The tournament is intended for Spanish players or residents in Spain, but each team is allowed one international player.
If you see a team looking for players in the list and you'd like to join them — or if you know a Spanish player you'd love to team up with — this is your chance to reach out!


By registering as an international player, you’re simply declaring your availability to join a team. Your name will appear in a public list that captains and other players can use to contact you if they’re looking for someone.


Tournament Link:
https://carcassonnespain.es/actividades/torneo-equipos-carcassonne-spain-tecs/

tournaments.about:
The Australian Carcassonne Online Championship is the annual national online championship for Australia. The winner is recognised as the online national champion for the year and has the opportunity to represent Australia at the annual in-person World Championships in Germany and also in the Carcassonne Champions League (CCL).

It is played on the Board Game Arena platform in 2 stages:
• A Swiss system automated tournament
• The top 4 players (or top 8 if there are more than 24 participants in round 1) progress to the playoffs
• Playoffs are Best of 3 games
• Preliminary playoffs are played if necessary

tournaments.about:
The US National Carcassonne Championship 2025 will take place online on August 30–31, 2025, starting at 9:00 AM Pacific / 12:00 PM Eastern each day.

• Day 1 (Saturday): Swiss-system preliminary rounds (6 games), run by the automated BGA tournament system.
• Day 2 (Sunday): Playoffs with the top 8 players from Day 1 in a single-elimination format (best-of-three duels).
All games will be played on Board Game Arena.

The winner will qualify to represent the USA at the World Carcassonne Championship in Essen, Germany on October 25, 2025.

Ukrainian Carcassonne Online Championship (UCOC) 2025 is a national tournament in which we play on the Board Game Arena (BGA) platform, in weekly one-on-one matches in the Best of Three format.

Each season takes place once a year, organized by player divisions with promotion and relegation. Only Ukrainian players are admitted to the championship.

In addition to enjoying the competition and the community built around Carcassonne, the winner of the top division of UCOC 2025 will get the chance to represent Ukraine in the Carcassonne Champions League 2026.

The tournament was recognized as the official Online Carcassonne Championship of Ukraine by Feelindigo, the publisher of the game in Ukraine.

tournaments.about:
Ukrainian Carcassonne Online Cup (UCOCup) 2024 is a national Carcassonne cup where we play on the Board Game Arena (BGA) platform in a Best of Three format (up to two wins).


Each such tournament takes place once a year and consists of two stages:
1. Double elimination (up to two losses) – an unlimited number of players can participate.
2. Knockout matches – the top 16 players who passed the Double elimination stage.
Only Ukrainian players are eligible to participate in the championship.


Dates: September 9 – November 11, 2024


In addition to the enjoyment of competition and the community built around Carcassonne, the winner of UCOCup 2024 will have the chance to represent Ukraine in the qualification tournament for the Carcassonne Champions League 2025.


The tournament was recognized as the official Online Carcassonne Cup of Ukraine by Feelindigo, the publisher of the game in Ukraine.
